<h3>Conditional <code>?:</code></h3>
<p>A quick way to assign a value to a variable based on a condition is with the ?: operator. Here is the form:</p>

<img class='wide' src='images/syntax_anatomy/conditional_operator.svg' onerror="this.src='images/syntax_anatomy/conditional_operator.png'" />
<p>Here is and example:</p>


<pre class="prettyprint">Game gameToPlay = doWeHaveEnergy ? futbol : chess;</pre>

<h3>Instance <code>instanceof</code></h3>
<p>To check if an object is an instance of a certain class, use <code>instanceof</code>. Here is the form:</p>
<img class='wide' src='images/syntax_anatomy/instanceof.svg' onerror="this.src='images/syntax_anatomy/instanceof.png'" />
<pre class="prettyprint">boolean isChessASport = chess instanceof Sport;</pre>

